  "title": "HAPwave_bids",
  "description": "This dataset comprises intracranial EEG recordings from 8 patients undergoing single-pulse electrical stimulation of limbic system structures. The data were collected to investigate electrical stimulation-driven network interactions in the human brain, with stimulation parameters of 200 microseconds duration, biphasic waveform, and 6 mA amplitude (4 mA for one subject). The dataset is organized according to BIDS specification and includes raw iEEG recordings with associated metadata and event timing information.",
  "methods_description": "Intracranial EEG recordings were obtained from 8 patients at rest in a hospital bed during single-pulse electrical stimulation. Stimulation parameters: 200 microsecond duration, biphasic waveform, 6 mA amplitude (4 mA for subject 7 to minimize interictal responses).",
